definition: down/downwards/below/lower/later/next (week etc)/second (of two parts)/to decline/to go down/to arrive at (a decision, conclusion etc)/measure word to show the frequency of an action

sentences.chinese: 公主殿下气派非凡地来了。

sentences.english: On Tuesday 23 May the keynote speaker will be His Royal Highness, The Prince of Wales.
sentences.chinese: 5月23日星期二的主旨发言人是威尔士亲王殿下。

sentences.english: It is too ugly for your highness's beautiful eyes.
sentences.chinese: 粗鄙得很，别污了殿下漂亮的眼睛。

sentences.english: The title of Royal Highness was to be restricted to the Duke alone.
sentences.chinese: 殿下的头衔仅仅授予了公爵一个人。

sentences.english: Your highness, I am always in the Central Palace serving the talent ladies.
sentences.chinese: 殿下，奴才一直在中宫伺候才人们。

sentences.english: "Your Imperial Highness, " he said with a bow.
We hear that Your Highness is an expert swordsman.
So not dare is leaving his highness king to explain what affair the white accurate took place?
sentences.chinese: 所以不敢在离王殿下说明白到底发生了什么事情？

sentences.english: To quote a favorite movie, "Life is pain, Highness.
sentences.chinese: 引用我喜欢的一部电影，“生活是痛苦的，殿下。

sentences.english: When Kate Middleton joins the House of Windsor this year, her official title will become 'Her Royal Highness the Princess William of Wales'.
sentences.chinese: 凯特今后的正式头衔就是“威尔士威廉王妃殿下”。

sentences.english: Prince, please forgive this shabby present.
sentences.chinese: 殿下，请原谅我献上这般菲薄的礼品。

sentences.english: The keynote speaker this year is His Royal Highness, The Prince of Wales.
sentences.chinese: 今年大会的主旨发言人是威尔士亲王殿下。

sentences.english: Twenty minutes later, after a royal joyride, his highness touched down.
sentences.chinese: 二十分钟后，殿下华丽地兜了一圈后，降落了。

sentences.english: Ma'am, you must appreciate that I have my duty to perform…just as Your Royal Highness has her duty.
sentences.chinese: 殿下，你得体谅我要尽忠职守，正如公主也有其职责。

sentences.english: The clattering crash you hear is the sound of Your Highness arriving at a theater near you.
sentences.chinese: 坠毁的辚你听到的是你的声音剧场附近殿下一抵达。

definition: courtier's or minister's form of address for the current Emperor
son of an official/son of nobility/your son (honorific)
state official or subject in dynastic China/I, your servant (used in addressing the sovereign)/Kangxi radical 131
crown prince/heir of a noble house
